Package: Tapas
Title: Taming the uncertainty of large language model in cell type annotation
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Author: Wen Tang <wxt175@case.edu>
Maintainer: Wen Tang <wxt175@case.edu>
Description: A R package to quantift the uncertainty of large language model (LLM) predictions in cell type annotation. 
 It takes as input the predicted cell type names generated by repeatedly prompting GPTCellType using the same cell type marker genes. 
 The core algorithm leverages the hierarchical structure of cell types and incorporates dissimilarity information derived from atlas-scale scRNA-seq data. 
 Tapas returns a p-value for each cell type per run, where a small p-value flags high heterogeneity and indicates lower confidence in the annotation results.
License: MIT
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: openai
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
